gV8(){return"The Rack"},
gV7(){return"The rack is the heart of GrooveForge. Each row is a slot \u2014 an independent instrument or effect processor. Add slots with the + button, remove them with the trash icon, and reorder them by dragging the handle on the left side of each slot."},
gVg(){return"Slot Types"},
gVe(){return"Keyboard"},
gVf(){return"Built-in FluidSynth driven by a soundfont (.sf2). Play from the on-screen keyboard or external MIDI. Choose None as the soundfont to use the keyboard as a MIDI-only controller (MIDI OUT cables in patch view, no built-in synth)."},
gVh(){return"Vocoder"},
gVi(){return"Processes microphone audio through a carrier wave for voice-synth effects."},
gVc(){return"Jam Mode"},
gVd(){return"Harmony engine that snaps incoming MIDI notes to a scale in real time. Receives chord information from a master keyboard slot."},
gVj(){return"VST3 Plugin"},
gVk(){return"Load any third-party VST3 instrument or effect. Requires a compatible .vst3 bundle installed on your system."},
gVl(){return"VST3 plugin slots are available on desktop platforms only (Linux, macOS, Windows). They are not available on Android or iOS."},
gVn(){return"Cable Patching"},
gV4(){return"The patch view lets you see the back panel of every slot in your rack and draw virtual cables between jacks, just like on a real hardware rack. Tap the cable icon in the top app bar to toggle between the front view (playing) and the back view (patching)."},
gVp(){return"Toggling Patch View"},
gVo(){return"Tap the cable icon (\u22a1) in the top-right of the rack screen to switch to the back panel view. Tap it again (or the agenda icon) to return to the front view. Slot reordering is disabled while in patch view."},
gV6(){return"Jack Types"},
gV5(){return"Each slot exposes a set of jacks grouped by signal family:\n\u2022 MIDI (yellow) \u2014 MIDI IN / MIDI OUT for note and CC messages.\n\u2022 Audio (red / white / orange) \u2014 AUDIO IN L, AUDIO IN R, AUDIO OUT L, AUDIO OUT R for stereo audio; SEND / RETURN for effects loops.\n\u2022 Data (purple) \u2014 CHORD OUT/IN and SCALE OUT/IN for Jam Mode harmony routing."},
gV3(){return"Drawing a Cable"},
gV2(){return"Long-press an output jack (\u25cf) to start dragging a cable. Compatible input jacks will pulse to show valid targets. Drag to a compatible input jack and release to connect. Dropping in empty space cancels the drag.\n\nCompatible pairs: MIDI OUT \u2192 MIDI IN, AUDIO OUT L \u2192 AUDIO IN L, AUDIO OUT R \u2192 AUDIO IN R, SEND \u2192 RETURN, CHORD OUT \u2192 CHORD IN, SCALE OUT \u2192 SCALE IN."},
gV1(){return"Disconnecting a Cable"},
gV0(){return"Each cable has a small \u2715 badge at its midpoint. Tap the badge to bring up the Disconnect menu. The badge is also the cable's hit zone, so aim for the circle with the coloured ring."},
gV_(){return"Data Cables (Jam Mode)"},
gUZ(){return"Purple data cables represent the Jam Mode harmony flow between slots. Drawing a CHORD OUT \u2192 CHORD IN cable is the same as selecting a Jam Mode master in the dropdown \u2014 both controls stay in sync. Similarly, a SCALE OUT \u2192 SCALE IN cable corresponds to a target follower slot."},
gVa(){return"One signal path per effect slot"},
gV9(){return"Audio effects (reverb, delay, chorus, harmonizer, wah, EQ, compressor, \u2026) hold internal filter state that is updated every audio block. An effect slot can therefore only be fed by one distinct signal path. Simple fan-in works: two keyboards cabled directly into the same reverb are mixed and processed together. Divergent paths do not: cabling kb1 \u2192 reverb AND kb2 \u2192 harmonizer \u2192 reverb asks the reverb to process two different signals in the same block, which would corrupt its filter state."},
gVb(){return"When GrooveForge blocks a cable with this rule, duplicate the effect slot so each signal path has its own instance. Add a second reverb from the plugin list and cable it into the second path."},
gVm(){return"Tip: Cables are saved as part of your project (.gf file). Open a saved project to restore all connections exactly as you left them."},
gUI(){return"Jam Mode (Auto-Harmony)"},
gUH(){return"Jam Mode allows you to play flawlessly by locking all keys to a specific scale. In Jam Mode, one channel acts as the 'Master' (transmitting its scale/harmony) while other channels act as 'Slaves'. Use the top controls to define the root note and scale type."},
gVB(){return"Vocoder (Voice Synth)"},
gJ0(){return"The Vocoder uses your device microphone to modulate the synth sound. Access it by selecting the 'VOCODER' preset in the soundfont dropdown. For best results:\n\u2022 Use wired headphones or speakers (latency over Bluetooth is too high).\n\u2022 Setup mic levels with the gain knobs.\n\u2022 Android Limitation: You cannot use separate USB devices for input and output. Use a single USB hub/interface that handles both, or the internal mic.\n\u2022 Experiment with different carrier waves (Saw, Pulse, Neutral)."},
gUY(){return"MIDI Connectivity"},
gUL(){return"Connect hardware controllers via USB (OTG adapter) or BLE MIDI. Enable CC Mapping in preferences to bind physical knobs to internal effects or system actions like 'Next Patch'."},
gUK(){return"Hardware Recommendations"},
gUJ(){return"For an optimal experience, we recommend using a split MIDI keyboard or a dual-keyboard setup:\n\u2022 Channel 2 (Left Hand): Send notes here to control chords and harmony (Jam Master).\n\u2022 Channel 1 (Right Hand): Use this channel to improvise over the generated harmony with the current scale."},
gVs(){return"Soundfonts (SF2)"},
gVr(){return"Import high-quality instrument sounds (.sf2) in the Soundfont preferences. Once loaded, you can assign them to any MIDI channel via the patch selector."},
gVz(){return"Musical Tips & Improvisation"},
gVy(){return"New to improvisation? Try these tips:\n\u2022 Scale as Safe Zone: Every key in the selected scale will sound 'correct' with the music.\n\u2022 The Root Note: Start or end your phrases on the root note (highlighted) to create a sense of resolution.\n\u2022 Rhythm first: Focus on simple rhythmic patterns rather than complex melodies."},
gVq(){return"Available Scales"},
